{{Quote|This fuel source we're after, the isotope-5&hellip; sergeant said it could change the course of the war.''"<br />"''Something better. Before we end up singing 'All Stars Burn as One.'|An Imperial [[Soldier/Legends|soldier]] mentions the Republic anthem while discussing the Galactic War with another Imperial soldier on the planet [[Makeb]]|<ref name="ROTHC">''[[Star Wars: The Old Republic: Rise of the Hutt Cartel]]''</ref>}}
"'''All Stars Burn as One'''", also known as the '''Republic Anthem''' or '''Anthem of the Republic''', was the official state [[Music/Legends|anthem]] of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] and had been composed by the [[Standard year/Legends|year]] [[3640 BBY]]. The anthem was generally played as a greeting at [[Diplomat/Legends|diplomatic]] and military meetings and was used by the Republic until it was [[Declaration of a New Order|reformed]] into the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] in [[19 BBY/Legends|19 BBY]]. At some point after the Empire was formed, [[Imperial Edict 2.33b]] forbade the playing of "All Stars Burn as One."

==Description==
{{Quote|If it were a ship's transponder, I could fix it, change it, make it sing the Republic anthem.|[[Tait Ransom]]|<ref name="WTDF">{{JournalCite|3|When the Domino Falls}}</ref>}}
"All Stars Burn as One" was a piece of [[Music/Legends|music]] that was used as the anthem of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]].<ref name="TCD" /> The anthem could be sung<ref name="WTDF" /> and had multiple stanzas. The piece was considered to have a martial sound by the [[Sullustan/Legends|Sullustan]] [[Journalist/Legends|journalist]] [[Den Dhur]]<ref name="MedStar I">''[[MedStar I: Battle Surgeons]]''</ref> and was thought to be a stirring piece of music by the [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]] [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] and the [[Vippit]] [[barrister]] [[Doolb Snoil]].<ref name="TCD" />

==History==
{{Quote|The Princess re-programmed the PA system to play the Anthem of the Republic (in direct violation of Imperial Edict 2.33b) during assembly.|Madam [[Nestor]] explaining one incident that led to Princess Leia Organa's expulsion from the Crevasse City Collegium for Young Ladies in a letter to Senator Bail Organa|<ref name="Star Wars: The Force Unleashed II">''[[Star Wars: The Force Unleashed II]]''</ref>}}
The piece of music titled "All Stars Burn as One" had been composed by [[3640 BBY]]. Between [[3643 BBY]] and that [[Standard year/Legends|year]],<ref name="Timeline" /> the music was the anthem of the Galactic Republic who was fighting the [[Galactic War]] against the [[Sith Empire (Post–Great Hyperspace War)|reconstituted Sith Empire]].<ref name="ROTHC" /> By [[22 BBY/Legends|22 BBY]],<ref name="NEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref> at the [[Time/Legends|time]] of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]] fought between the Republic and the [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Confederacy of Independent Systems]], "All Stars Burn as One" was still the anthem of the Republic. While the song excited the Jedi Knight Obi-Wan Kenobi at one point in his life, the tense [[Politics/Legends|political]] and militaristic situations that permeated the Clone Wars eventually made hearing the song uncomfortable for him.<ref name="TCD" />

During the war, around the year 22 BBY,<ref name="ERC">''[[The Essential Reader's Companion]]''</ref> Kenobi was [[Mission to Ord Cestus|sent]] to the prison [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Ord Cestus/Legends|Ord Cestus]] to prevent the sale of the [[Force-sensitive/Legends|Force-sensitive]] [[JK-13 security droid]]s, which posed a significant threat to [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]]. Upon his arrival in Ord Cestus's [[Capital/Legends|capital]], [[ChikatLik]], a [[Band/Legends|band]] of [[musician droid]]s greeted the Knight's party with renditions of the [[Cestian anthem]] and "All Stars Burn as One."<ref name="TCD" /> The anthem was also played when a high-ranking [[Officer/Legends|officer]] or visiting dignitary would arrive at a Republic site.<ref name="MedStar I" /> In [[20 BBY/Legends|20 BBY]],<ref name="ERC" /> the anthem was played when [[Admiral/Legends|Admiral]] [[Tarnese Bleyd]] arrived to inspect [[Republic Mobile Surgical Unit/Legends|Republic Mobile Surgical Unit]] [[Republic Mobile Surgical Unit 7|7]] during a [[Battle of Drongar|battle]] on the planet [[Drongar/Legends|Drongar]].<ref name="MedStar I" />

At some point after<ref name="TFU2">''[[Star Wars: The Force Unleashed II]]'' {{C|[[Wikipedia:PlayStation 3|PS3]]/[[Wikipedia:Xbox 360|Xbox 360]] databank}}</ref> the Republic [[Declaration of a New Order|became]] the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] in [[19 BBY/Legends|19 BBY]],<ref name="NEC" /> the Empire passed a law known as [[Imperial Edict 2.33b]] that forbade the playing of "All Stars Burn as One."<ref name="TFU2" /> Around the year [[12 BBY/Legends|12 BBY]],<ref name="LeiaDate">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' establishes that [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]] was [[Reproduction/Legends|born]] in [[19 BBY/Legends|19 BBY]]. ''[[Star Wars: The Force Unleashed II]]'' {{C|[[Wikipedia:PlayStation 3|PS3]]/[[Wikipedia:Xbox 360|Xbox 360]] databank}} states that [[Princess/Legends|Princess]] Leia Organa was seven [[Standard year/Legends|years]] old when she was expelled from [[Crevasse City Collegium for Young Ladies]]. Therefore she was expelled around the year [[12 BBY/Legends|12 BBY]].</ref> [[Princess/Legends|Princess]] [[Leia Organa Solo/Legends|Leia Organa]] of the planet [[Alderaan/Legends|Alderaan]] tampered with the public address system during an assembly at the [[Crevasse City Collegium for Young Ladies|Collegium for Young Ladies]] in [[Crevasse City (Alderaan)/Legends|Crevasse City]], [[Programmer/Legends|re-programming]] the device to play the forbidden anthem. The incident was one of several that prompted the Collegium's Board of Directors to expel the [[Gender/Legends|girl]] from the school and return her [[Bail Prestor Organa/Legends|father's]] 30,000 [[Galactic Credit Standard/Legends|credit]] bond.<ref name="TFU2" />

==Behind the scenes==
The Galactic Republic's anthem was first mentioned in "[[When the Domino Falls]]," a [[1994]] short story written by [[Patricia A. Jackson]] for [[West End Games]]' [[Star Wars Adventure Journal 3|third issue]] of the ''[[Star Wars Adventure Journal]]''.<ref name="WTDF" /> In [[2004]], the Republic anthem was given the name, "All Stars Burn as One," when the anthem made its first appearance in ''[[The Cestus Deception]]'', a novel written by [[Steven Barnes]].<ref name="TCD" /> In [[2011]], the [[BioWare]] [[Star Wars video games|video game]] ''[[Star Wars: The Old Republic]]'' featured a bonus quest series on the planet [[Balmorra/Legends|Balmorra]] where the Galactic Republic&ndash;affiliated player is tasked with changing the music in the Sith Empire&ndash;controlled [[Sunken Sarlacc cantina]] to something more patriotic.<ref name="Patriotic">{{TORcite|type=faction|Republic|A Clean Sweep|Balmorra}}</ref> The music that is played when the player completes that part of the quest is the same as the [[Revan's theme|Old Republic theme]] from the [[2003]] video game ''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic]]'', which also serves as [[Revan/Legends|Revan's]] theme and the main theme.<ref name="KotOR">''[[Star Wars: Knights of the Old Republic]]''</ref> However, the game does not state whether the music played is the Republic anthem.<ref name="Patriotic" />

